Long story short, I ended up with this vest in place of a crappy pistol and some cash. In my rather mundane and suburban middle class life, I am rarely if ever in need of such accrutriments. As such, make me an offer - I would like to trade. I am building an AR and need lower parts (Giselle trigger, Stock, BCG etc) but, as my possession of the vest shows, open to completely random offers if they are cool. 

This comes with the vest, brand new, neck liner/collar and cod (dong) protector. These are soft kevlar, meant to protect from shrapnel and small pistol rounds. To valiantly/stupidly stand in front of any real firepower, you will need to invest in a ceramic or steel set of plates. Or dont... just dont come trying to get a refund when you have gone and gotten yourself all shot full of holes. 

These are not military walk-offs; when they replaced these with the newer models with the kidney plates and better drag tags the remaining contract vests were sold.

title: For Sale:  6.5 Grendel AA Overwatch upper on Bushy lower
postcontent:
As much as it pains me to do so, I am offering up for sale my 6.5 Grendel. Now, I know the paint job will not be appealing to most, but I never intended to sell it, and I wanted to paint it, so there ya go. Anyway, the rifle is a Bushmaster lower with an Alexander Arms Overwatch upper on it. I bought this from an older benchrest shooter who thought it would be fun to shoot an AR, but he never got used to the recoil spring noise……. Everything else he shot was a bolt gun. Go figure. He had someone install a trigger over travel adjustment screw into the selector – I’ve never seen that before, but it’s pretty cool. It’s in one of the pics. I replaced the factory handguard with a Yankee Hill free float quad rail, and added the rings and 20x Super Sniper scope. Will ship with Lee dies, two boxes of Alexander Arms ammo (three rounds missing from one box), and a bag of loaded and empty rounds (gotta dig the bag up so I can get an accurate count), and three magazines. (I have a 5 rounder, but it didn’t make it into the pic – but it’s here.)
I bought this rifle to use as a coyote rifle, hence the paint job, but I have yet to fire a round thru it. I haven’t had the time to work with it, and have decided to sell it and put the money towards an old CJ7 rebuild project.

postcontent: Family Firearms Sales located at 3866 Maizeland Rd in Colorado Springs is looking for a qualified Store Coordinator.Main Responsibilities: - Ensuring store is organized and clean - Shipping and receiving - Background checks and 4473 form processing - Checking of layways and holds - Helping with sales during busy times - Inventory of store, item labeling, etc. - Box and garbage removal - Answer phones with sales staff is busy - All other duties as assignedRequirements: - Must be able to lift up to 75lbs - Must be able to reach up, down and crouch to get store inventory - Must be very friendly and able to communicate with staff and customers effectively - Must have a high attention to details and be able to spot small errors on forms easily - you will be tested - Must be computer saavy and be able to use e-mail, PDF files, our Point of Sale and Inventory system as well as shipping carrier websites to create labels, etc. - Must be highly reliable and prompt - Must have reliable transportation to work and ability to take parcels to Post Office and UPS hub on a daily basis (mileage reimbursed) - so must have vehicle to carry parcels (most easily fit into a normal vehicle) - Must be able to follow directions effectively - Must have at least a basic knowledge of firearms and accessories - Must be energetic, able to multi-task, time manage, and self motivated - able to complete tasks with little supervision - Prior retail experience and customer service preferredPay and Benefits: - This job starts at $10.00 an hour - 40 hours a week (full-time/Permanent only) - Current work days needed: Monday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday - Two weeks paid vacation per year starting - No current health or retirement benefits.Family Firearms Sales is a growing, locally owned, firearms retailer. We are committed to customer service and industry leading friendliness in our stores. If you fit the above requirments and think you have what it takes to be an asset to our fast-paced store, please e-mail your resume to REDACTED or drop it off in-person at the store.
